SUMMARY:On a Clear Day...New landscape paintings by Phil Gross
DESCRIPTION:Right where we live’ is the subject of Phil Gross’s art show\, ‘On a clear day…’.\nGross’s oil paintings of northern California from aerial and ground perspectives can best be described as idealistic realism. Through a rearrangement of the objects along with a deliberate balancing act of colors\, his compositions invite you to take a deeper look at the places you already know. “I want you to have an overwhelming feeling that with the next step you will suddenly be right in the painting\, breathing in the lusciousness of our latitude.” \nReception: Friday March 13 6-9 pm
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/on-a-clear-day-new-landscape-paintings-by-phil-gross/
LOCATION:The Artery\, 207 G Street\, Davis\, CA
CATEGORIES:Art
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Phil-Gross-Cherry-Glen-large-scaled.jpeg
