SUMMARY:Dancing Through Life\, a Jazz Choir Cabaret
DESCRIPTION:The Davis Senior High School Jazz Choir invites the community to experience two unforgettable evenings of music\, movement\, and show-stopping performances at its annual Jazz Choir Cabaret\, taking place Friday and Saturday\, March 20 and 21\, 2026\, at the Richard Brunelle Performance Hall on the Davis Senior High School campus. \nThe cabaret-style evening offers more than just a concert—it’s a full entertainment experience. Audiences can expect a high-energy production featuring the full Jazz Choir\, standout soloists\, and small group numbers that blend jazz\, pop\, and contemporary vocal styles with polished choreography. \nTwo Viewing Options on Friday and Saturday: \nDinner & Show ($55): Enjoy an exclusive dining experience with mocktails and a catered dinner provided by Simply Satisfied Catering Co. in the Choir Room\, along with live entertainment from the Jazz Choir and Jazz Band Ensemble. After dinner\, guests will be escorted to reserved seating for the 7:00 PM performance. \nShow Only ($30) and Show Only – Student ($15): For those attending only the performance\, doors open at 6:45 PM. Guests will be treated to mocktails and the opportunity to participate in the raffle before the show starts at 7:00 PM. \nProceeds from the Jazz Choir Cabaret directly support the Davis Senior High School Jazz Choir program\, helping fund music\, choreography\, costumes\, and performance opportunities for students throughout the year.
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/dancing-through-life-a-jazz-choir-cabaret-2/
LOCATION:Richard Brunelle Performance Hall\, 315 W 14th Street\, Davis\, CA\, 95616\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bring the Kids,Community,Food & Drink,Music,Stage & Dance
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Dancing-Through-Life-SM.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Davis Jazz Choir%2C Inc.":MAILTO:davisjazzchoir@gmail.com
